org.dice_research.squirrel.deduplication.hashing.impl

Class SimpleTripleComparator

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.dice_research.squirrel.deduplication.hashing.impl.SimpleTripleComparator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TripleComparator

    public class SimpleTripleComparator
extends Object
implements TripleComparator
    A simple implementation of TripleComparator which just iterates over the sets of triples and compares them one by one. Note: The comparator can possibly return true for two lists of triples that are in fact not equal. If the two lists contain duplicates of different triples, there sizes can be equal, and they can still be equal after converting the lists to sets. By converting the lists to sets, duplicates are removed and therefore precision is lost. But we chose to use sets for better performance. A more precise comparison could be done in future, it can get quite complex if a good performance is desired.
